Fourth, through entering markets or courts, where others come to trade;
Fifth, through ignorance of ritual statutes, secretly grasping at its solemn forms;
Sixth, through single-minded reverence for a master, receiving instruction and transmission;
Seventh, through family ancestors, passing it down through generations.

These seven conditions may occur separately or in combination, varying in rank and circumstance, each with its own covenantal rites—transmission by a master being central.

The proper procedures are as follows:

Ascend the Jade Clarity Imperial Altar to pledge vows and transmit the scriptural instructions. The altar shall be twenty-four feet in length and breadth, with four corner gates. Five-colored patterned silks, one bolt each for the five directions; ninety feet of purple silk; ninety feet of azure gauze; nine taels of gold; forty feet of life-destiny silk; five seating mats; one golden fish and one jade dragon; one jade tablet, twelve inches long and two inches four-tenths wide; five ritual boards for the Five Agents; three talismans; five incense fires; one crimson silk kerchief, five feet long; one foot of white silk; one gold ring; five luminous mirrors; fifteen feet of white silk for inscribing the covenant text; the covenant document bound with blue silk and a gold clasp, with twenty feet of crossed sashes in purple and damask patterns.

The earth-altar shall be of plain silk, matching the imperial altar in dimensions—twenty-four feet in length and breadth—with four corner gates. Five taels of gold shall be placed above, with nine feet of white silk as sashes and three feet two inches of purple silk.

On the day before the transmission, the recipient shall fast at the altar site. Facing north, he shall knock his teeth nine times and pray aloud:

“Supreme Primordial Sovereign, Numinous Honored One of the Nine Heavens, the Most Real in the distant and profound Jade Pavilion—guided by the revolutions of the Three and Five, the dawns of the Seven Luminaries shifting, the Void Emperor holding the reins, the Jade Emperor determining immortality—on this day of primal auspiciousness, the myriad perfected open the way. Those who ascend to the ranks of the celestial stems, bound by karmic destiny, encounter the divine scriptures, the treasured scrolls of the Supreme Sovereign. Humbly, upon this sacred peak, I pledge vows to the Nine Heavens, petition the Five Emperors and the Twelve River Sources, beseeching registration and receipt. May my plea ascend to the lofty court, universally proclaimed to the ten thousand spirits. Here, upon the imperial altar, defenses are arrayed to dispel trials, following the precedents of the Great Perfected. Tomorrow, at the appointed hour, the transmission shall proceed.”

At dawn on the day of ascension, thirty paces from the altar, the recipient shall knock his teeth thirty-two times, envisioning purple clouds crowning a mountain and the divine soldiers of the Five Emperors—thousands upon thousands—coming to welcome his person. He shall softly intone:

“The divine perfected roam forth, startling the myriad emperors. The Jade Numinous Mystic Guardians, the wardens of the Five Peaks, the Celestial Soldiers and Mighty Warriors—ten thousand strong—assist the numinous. Summoned from the ten directions, marshaling the heavenly hosts, they descend from the heavens to the imperial court. May I ascend as an immortal, penetrating the essence of the Dao. May I discern the inauspicious, traverse the hidden, and fathom the obscure. All that I face and declare shall align with the Jade Clarity.”

This completed, he shall ascend the altar.

The master enters from the northwest, facing northwest to perform nine bows toward the Nine Heavenly Kings, knocking his teeth nine times. He shall softly declare:

“Today, I transmit the Nine Heavens’ Treasured Scripture to Disciple Wang Ding, extending to the Jade Taboo. Having fasted and purified, his qi and destiny harmonize with the Real. I beseech the oversight of the Perfected Immortals and the Jade Taboo. May the Registrar Attendant and the Guardian Marshal of the Numinous descend to witness the covenant in heaven. May all that is petitioned and entrusted swiftly ascend for audience.”

This completed, he turns to the southeast, bows again, and declares:

“Supreme Primordial Heaven, today I offer the Eight Assemblies’ vows. On this auspicious day and pure hour, humbly upon this sacred peak, I pledge vows to transmit the supreme scripture. I beseech the divine immortals of the Five Emperors to oversee my covenant, that I may swiftly attain immortality, ascend in a flying chariot, and rise to the imperial court.”

The disciple enters from the southeast below the altar, performs nine bows to the northwest, then two bows to the southeast. Turning north to face the master, he knocks his teeth thirty-six times, first reciting the *Golden Perfected Great Void Chapter* once to subdue the myriad demons.

This chapter derives from the *Golden Perfected Jade Radiance Scroll*. Without receiving the *Supreme Clarity Jade Radiance*, one may not recite this text.

The celestial essence rides the void, startling the divine court.
Entrusted to the immortal’s chant, it transforms into the nameless.
How tumultuous the clamorous qi, the defiled Dao arising along the path!
Within the clouds, the Crimson Palace; the Northern Emperor deploys his divine soldiers.
The drum resounds from the ocean of wisdom, the mysterious workings come to welcome.
The lofty scenes feast upon flying reins, swift chariots inspect the cloud encampments.
Hastening to collate the Northern Emperor’s register, seizing the names of the demonic hordes.
The *Huoluo* unfurls the celestial net, wielding might to cast the ringing bells.
Now the perfected capture the empty cavern, the jade radiance illuminating the eight darknesses.
The Golden Mystery guards the supreme palace, the divine tiger slays the celestial essence.
Severing the myriad demonic qi, billions upon billions all leveled.
Upholding the trust of the Nine Heavens, all is overthrown at my whistled command.
Summoning the perfected to fathom the Three Caverns, wisdom recitation clears the eyes.
Gazing upon the eight paths of the mysterious radiance, seven revolutions weave the celestial scriptures.
Merging with the imperial unity of the Real, delivering the seven generations of ancestors.
Eradicating the roots of the five sufferings, the returned soul receives renewed glory.
The golden radiance shines upon the quiescent, the divine candle naturally kindles.
Fragrant blossoms scatter in the jade palace, misty qi penetrates the Jade Capital.
The Emperor dispatches the lingering chariot, the Three Origins descend in green carriages.
Swift chariots soar through the Nine Mysteries, paying homage at the Jade Emperor’s court.”

Upon completing the *Great Void Chapter*, the disciple faces east, knocks his teeth thirty-six times, and intones:

“Supreme Three Heavens’ Primordial Qi of the Mysterious Origin, Most High Lord Lao, summon forth from within my person the Void-and-Spontaneous Flying Immortal Attendants, the Divine Immortal Envoys, the Left and Right Flying Dragons, the Great Perfected Jade Maidens, and the Direct Talismans of the Five Emperors—thirty-six each—to report to the local earth deities and true officials. As I now burn incense, may my petition swiftly reach the boundless Jade Emperor and the Most High Perfected before the myriad sages.”

This completed, he faces north, knocks his teeth twenty-four times, and exits the *Supreme Clarity Office*.

Without receiving the *Supreme Clarity Three Origins Jade Inspection*, one may not exit this office.

“Reverently, I summon from within my person:
The Void-and-Spontaneous Left and Right Jade Void Attendants, twenty-four each;
The Void-and-Spontaneous Five Emperors of the Great Perfected, twenty-four each;
The Void-and-Spontaneous Left and Right Jade Immortal-Guiding Attendants, twenty-four each;
The Nine Mysteries’ Void-and-Spontaneous Flying Dragon Attendants, twenty-four each;
The Upper Origin Attendants, twenty-four each;
The Middle Origin Attendants, twenty-four each;
The Lower Origin Attendants, twenty-four each;
The *Supreme Clarity Jade Void* Flying Immortal Envoys, twenty-four each;
The Divine Immortal Envoys, twenty-four each;
The Jade Immortal Envoys, twenty-four each;
The Great Immortal Envoys, twenty-four each;
The Upper Origin Envoys, twenty-four each;
The Middle Origin Envoys, twenty-four each;
The Lower Origin Envoys, twenty-four each;
The *Jade Clarity Golden Dawn* Jade Lads, twenty-four each;
The *Jade Clarity Great Florescence* Jade Maidens, twenty-four each.”

Those who emerge do so with solemn dignity, clad in immortal robes, their majesty and decorum perfectly composed as they stand arrayed before the minister.

The Jade Void Attendant Ministers wear soaring-dark-jade crowns, robes of nine-colored dragon-patterned tiger-skins, and wield the Banner of Commanding Demons, standing to the left.

The Five Thearchs’ Supreme Perfected wear Primordial Dawn Jade Crowns, five-colored flying-immortal feathered robes, and nine-colored pennants, standing to the right.

The Flying Dragon Attendants wear Level-Heaven Jade Crowns, nine-colored phoenix robes, tiger-script belts, and hold the Talismans of Summoning Spirits, positioned above.

The Three Origins Attendants wear Nine Origins Vermilion Yang Jade Crowns, three-colored feathered robes, belts of flowing-gold fire-bells, and wield the Statutes of Seizing and Slaying, standing below.

The Flying Immortal Envoys wear Soaring Heaven Jade Crowns, nine-colored variegated-patterned robes, and hold golden talismans with banners raised before them.

The Divine Immortal Envoys wear Vermilion Yang Jade Crowns, flying-immortal feathered robes, jade tablets in hand, and bear standards behind them.

The *Great Void’s Spontaneous Celestial-Auxiliary Immortal Flying Dark Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Celestial-Auxiliary Perfected Flying Ascending Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Celestial-Auxiliary Divine Flying Marching Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Celestial-Auxiliary Thearch Ascending Void Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Celestial-Auxiliary Spirit Ascending Void Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Great Void’s Spontaneous Five Thearchs’ Flying Immortal Sky-Strategizing Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad chariots;
The *Great Void’s Spontaneous Flying Immortal Ascending Void Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad chariots;
The *Spontaneous Flying Jade-Feather Canopy Bridle-Holding Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad chariots;
The *Spontaneous Flying Green Carriage Bridle-Holding Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad chariots;
The *Spontaneous Celestial-Regulating Earth-Commanding Dragon Ascending Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad chariots;
The *Spontaneous Summoning Perfected Zhi-Mushroom Jade Immortal Clerks*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Spontaneous Divine Elixir Birth Immortal Clerks*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Spontaneous Golden Perfected Flowing Light Radiant Lightning Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Spontaneous Yin Essence Cloud-Raising Rain-Descending Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Yang Brightness Shining Summons-qi Pursuing Lightning Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number;
The *Spontaneous Cloud Gate Banner-Holding Commanding Light Cavalry*, nine hundred million myriad in number—
all these divine immortal troops and cavalry assemble and encamp, stationed before, behind, left, and right of the minister, arrayed in ordered ranks.

Spontaneous five-colored flowing rosy clouds and purple mists, nine hundred million myriad layers;
Spontaneous Five Thearchs’ flying wheels and flowing mists, nine hundred million myriad layers;
Five-colored flying jade-feather canopies, nine hundred million myriad layers;
Five Peaks’ five-colored flying carriages, nine hundred million myriad layers—
envelop the minister’s form, streaming essence and dispersing qi, filling the ten directions, encircling heaven and covering earth, guarding and protecting the minister’s body.

Once the solemn proceedings conclude, the feathered-node-bearing flying immortal jade lads hold aloft jade tables suspended in the void, positioned before the minister, receiving the words from the minister’s mouth to distinguish and report to the celestial officials, earth deities, and gods of the four directions, central quarters, ten directions, Five Peaks, Four Waterways, Nine Rivers, Eight Poles, famous mountains, great marshes, Five Thearchs’ Perfected Officials, Four Departments’ Inspectors, Nine Divisions’ Examiners and Summoners, Primordial Qi’s *Jiazi* Official Lords, boundless, measureless, depthless, heightless, fathomless, obscure or manifest, innumerable Perfected Officials; infusing qi into the Qian Sovereign’s Nine Palaces, Eight Trigrams, Six *Jia* Perfected Ones; the Void’s Direct Servants, Five Peaks’ Flying Immortals, divine dragon feathered cavalry.

The qi ascends to report to the Primordial Origin August Supreme High Void Jade Emperor, the Nine Heavens’ Venerable One;
the Primordial Origin Three Heavens’ Jade Lads, Supreme Numinous Perfected Kings;
the Highest Myriad Immortals’ Fusang Great Emperor;
the Supreme Great Dao Jade Dawn Lord;
the Three Origins Southern Culmen Prohibited Lord;
the Golden Watchtower Posterior Sage Emperor Lord;
the Eastern Florescence Azure Lad;
the Four Poles’ Perfected Ones;
the Thirty-Nine Emperors;
the Twenty-Four Perfected;
the Supreme Clarity Primordial Origin Upper Three Heavens’ Boundless Great Dao;
the Supreme Lord Lao;
the Supreme Venerable One;
the Heavenly Elder Emperor Lord;
the Nine Elders’ Immortal Capital Lord;
the Nine Qi Venerable One;
the Boundless Supreme Unity Emperor Lord—
and the hundred thousand myriad layers of Dao-qi, the twelve hundred official lords, the Supreme Clarity Jade Steps’ Celestial Immortals, Divine Immortals, Flying Immortals, Five Thearchs’ Immortal Lords, Great Florescence Perfected Ones.

The minister, by karmic affinity and accumulated blessings, has endured the kalpas of the Nine Heavens, revolving without extinction, favored by fortune to be born into the Dharma-gate. Formerly, through the grace of former sagely perfected ones, he was uplifted and guided, his ignorance dispelled, and the supreme methods revealed to him—the Great Secrets of the Nine Heavens, the Three Caverns’ Treasured Scriptures, Jade Talismans, Numinous Writings, Cinnabar Scripts in Purple Characters, Flying Void Step Chapters—ascending the imperial altar to report and command the Nine Heavens. Over the years, as celestial cycles shifted and the imperial Dao’s destiny unfolded, the Dharma was to be transmitted to later disciples, those with predestined immortal names and destined for transcendence. The numinous texts are secret and weighty; they dare not be withheld, nor lightly transmitted. According to the stipulated time limits, should the kalpas turn, even the most devoted scholars might forever lack the affinity, their aspirations cut off, their efforts in vain. Yet when the Primordial Origin opens the transformation, it is rare to encounter the right person—thus, by the principles of the mysterious statutes, when the encounter aligns, the transmission is granted.

Now there is the Master of Such-and-Such Peak, Wang of *Jia* clan, whose accumulated blessings and surplus fortune have met with this era of flourishing prosperity. By karmic good fortune, he was born in this sagely age, favored by the Supreme to have his name inscribed in the imperial records, to partake in the great Dharma, and to recite the Jade Scriptures. Over the years, he has cast aside worldly attachments, forgotten his shadow, and entrusted his aspirations to secluded peaks, calming his spirit in mountain caves, contemplating the numinous and meditating on qi. Yet his understanding remains shallow and narrow, and he has not yet mastered all matters. Now, he again approaches the minister, observing a seven-day purification fast, submitting his vows and oaths, seeking completion and establishment. He erects the imperial altar, reports to the Nine Heavens, and receives the Supreme Clarity’s Treasured Secrets and Jade Scriptures—all such matters as required. With faith and oaths fully prepared, all in accordance with the statutes and methods, the minister then escorts him to ascend the numinous mountain, reporting to the Five Peaks and Five Thearchs, and announcing to the Nine Heavens to transmit the teachings to him.

He pledges to observe silence in his practice, never to be negligent, never to reveal the true texts, nor to violate the statutes or transgress the precepts. Should he do so, his seven generations of ancestors will be examined, and his own person will be delivered to the ghostly officials.

